015}} \n|- align=\"center\"\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Operazione San Pietro]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n| English: ''Operation Saint Peter's''\n|- align=\"center\"\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Due RRRingos nel Texas]]''\n|\n| \n| {{yes}} (cameo)\n| English: ''Two Ringos in Texas''<ref>Howarth, Troy (2015). Splintered Visions: Lucio Fulci and his Films. Midnight Marquee Press. Filmography section</ref>\n|- align=\"center\"\n| align=\"center\"| 1968\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[I due crociati]]''\n|\n| {{yes}} (co-writer)\n|\n| English: ''The Two Crusaders''; (directed by Giuseppe Orlandini)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| rowspan=3 align=\"center\"| 1969\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Double Face]]''\n|\n| {{yes}} (co-writer/ co-plotter)\n|\n| Italian: ''A doppia faccia''; a.k.a. ''Liz and Helen''; a.k.a. ''Das Gesicht im Dunkeln'' / ''The Face in the Dark'', a.k.a. ''Chaleur et jouissance / Heat and Pleasure'' (a more adult re-edit); (Fulci only contributed to the story, film was directed by [[Riccardo Freda]]){{sfn|Howarth|2015|p=56}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Una sull'altra]]'' (''One on Top of the Other'')\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}} (cameo as handwriting expert)\n| Translation: ''One on Top of the Other''; a.k.a. ''Perversion Story''; (released theatrically in USA in 1973){{sfn|Howarth|2015}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[The Conspiracy of Torture|Beatrice Cenci]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n| a.k.a. ''The Conspiracy of Torture'' (USA); (released theatrically in USA in 1976){{sfn|Howarth|2015}} \n|- align=\"center\"\n| align=\"center\"| 1971\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[A Lizard in a Woman's Skin]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n| Italian: ''Una lucertola con la pelle di donna'';  a.k.a. ''Schizoid'', a.k.a. ''Carole''\n|- align=\"center\"\n| rowspan=4 align=\"center\"| 1972\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Hector the Mighty]]''\n|\n| {{yes}} (co-writer)\n|\n| Italian: ''Ettore lo fusto''; (directed by Enzo Castellari){{sfn|Howarth|2015|p=59}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| align