 this film as well){{sfn|Howarth|2015}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| 1991\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Voices from Beyond]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}} (co-written with Piero Regnoli)\n| {{yes}} (cameo as pathologist)\n| Italian: ''Voci dal profondo'' / ''Voices From The Deep''\n|- align=\"center\"\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Door to Silence]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}} \n|\n| Italian: ''Le porte del silenzio''; a.k.a. ''El Enigma de la Muerte'', produced by Joe D'Amato{{sfn|Howarth|2015|p=341}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| align=\"center\"| 1997\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[The Wax Mask]]''\n|\n| {{yes}} (co-writer only)\n|\n| a.k.a. ''[[The Wax Mask|MDC: Maschera di cera]]'', a.k.a. ''[[Wax Mask]]'' (released posthumously)\n|}\n\n=== Films \"presented\" by Lucio Fulci ===\n\n* '''''The Murder Secret''''' (1988, a.k.a. ''Non avere paura della zia Marta'' / ''Don't Be Afraid of Aunt Martha'', a.k.a. ''Aunt Martha Does Dreadful Things'', a.k.a. ''El espejo roto'') \u2013 Fulci supervised the gore effects on this film which was written and directed by [[Mario Bianchi]], and was credited as a co-producer.{{sfn|Howarth|2015|p=342}}\n* '''''[[The Red Monks]]''''' (1988, a.k.a. ''I Frati Rossi'', a.k.a. ''Sexorgien der roten M\u00f6nche''){{sfn|Howarth|2015|p=342}}  Fulci fought in vain to have his name removed from this film's credits; the film was directed and co-written by [[Gianni Martucci]] whom Fulci claimed he never even met.{{sfn|Howarth|2015|p=344}} Fulci was credited with handling the film's special effects, which he later denied having been involved with.<ref>Paul, Louis (2011). \"Italian Horror Film Directors\". McFarland & Co., Inc. {{ISBN|978-0-7864-6113-4}}. Page 132</ref>\n* '''''Hansel and Gretel''''' (1989, a.k.a. ''Non Si Seviziano i Bambini'' / ''Don't Torture the Children'', a.k.a. ''Die saat des teufels''/ ''The Devil's Seed'').{{sfn|Howarth|2015|p=342}} Fulci later directed additional footage that was inserted into this Giovanni Simonelli film to lengthen its running time. Simonelli both wrote and directed the film.{{sfn|Howarth|2015|p=343}} This film was never dubbed in English.\n* '''''Massacre'''''/ ''Massacro'' (1989, a.k.a. ''La morte della medium''/ ''The Death of the Medium''; a.k.a. ''Remember Dr. Jekyll'') \u2013 Fulci lent his name as co-producer on this film which was written and directed by [[Andrea Bianchi]], although he claimed he was hardly involved at all with making it. This film was never dubbed in English.{{sfn|Howarth|2015|p=344}}\n* '''''Bloody Psycho''''' (1989, a.k.a. ''The Snake House'', a.k.a. ''Pesadilla Sangrienta'', a.k.a. ''Lo Specchio'' / ''The Mirror'',  a.k.a. ''Nel Nido del Serpente'' / ''In the Nest of the Serpent''){{sfn|Thrower|1999}} \u2013 Fulci lent his name as co-producer on this film directed and co-written by Leandro Luchetti; Fulci's involvement is dubious. This film was never dubbed in English.\n* '''''Escape from Death'''''/ ''Fuga dalla Morte'' (1989, a.k.a. ''Luna di Sangue''/ ''Moon of Blood''){{sfn|Howarth|2015|p=342}} \u2013 Fulci lent his name as co-producer on this film directed and co-written by Enzo Milioni; Fulci's involvement is dubious. This film was never dubbed in English.{{sfn|Howarth|2015|p=344}}\n\n== Accolades ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Film\n! Result\n|-\n|1983\n|[[Fantasporto]] Film Festival\n|[[International Fantasy Film Award]]\n|''[[The House by the Cemetery]]''\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1986\n|[[Avoriaz]] Fantastic Film Festival\n|Fear Section Award\n|''[[Murder Rock]]''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== Bibliography ==\n* {{cite book |last=Cacciatore |first=Giacomo; Albiero, Paolo |title=Il terrorista dei generi, tutto il cinema di Lucio Fulci |publisher=Un mondo a parte |location=[[Rome]], Italy |year=2004}}\n* {{cite book |last=Thrower |first=Stephen |title=Beyond Terror, the films of Lucio Fulci |publisher=FAB Press |year=1999 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Bruschini | first=Antonio|title=Lucio Fulci, il poeta della crudelt\u00e0|year=2004|publisher=Mondo Ignoto|isbn=88-89084-25-1}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Tentori |first1=Antonio|last2=Cozzi|first2=Luigi|title=Guida al cinema horror made in Italy|year=2004|publisher=Profondo Rosso Edizioni|isbn=978-88-95294-03-2}}\n* {{cite book |last=Julien |first=S\u00e9v\u00e9on|title=Lucio Fulci - le po\u00e8te du macabre|year=2009|publisher=Bazaar&Co|isbn=978-2-917339-12-1}}\n* {{cite book |last=Balun |first=Chas |authorlink=Chas Balun |author2=[special introduction by Antonella Fulci] |title=Lucio Fulci: Beyond the Gates |edition=2nd |location=[[Key West, Florida|Key West]], [[Florida]] |publisher=Fantasma Books |year=1997 |isbn=1-888214-07-4}}\n* {{cite book |last=Howarth |first=Troy |year=2015 |title=Splintered Visions: Lucio Fulci and his Films |publisher=Midnight Marquee Press |ref=harv}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|2086}}\n* [http://www.shockingimages.com/fulci/menu.html Shocking Images \u2013 tribute website]\n\n{{Lucio Fulci}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fulci, Lucio}}\n[[Category:1927 births]]\n[[Category:1996 deaths]]\n[[Category:Italian film directors]]\n[[Category:Horror film directors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Rome]]\n[[Category:Spaghetti Western directors]]\n[[Category:Italian screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Italian male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Writers from Rome]]\n[[Category:Italian Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Deaths from diabetes]]\n[[Category:Giallo film directors]]\n[[Category:20th-century Italian male actors]]\n", "name_user": "HorrorProfessor", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lucio_Fulci"}
{"title_page": "Darul Huda Islamic University", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Confusing|date=December 2019}}\n{{Original research|date=December 2019}}\n}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name            = Darul Huda Islamic University\n| logo_size       = \n| native_name     = \u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629 \u062f\u0627\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0647\u062f\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645\u064a\u0629\n| image_name      = Darul Huda.jpg\n| caption         = Main Entrance of Darul Huda Islamic University\n| image_size      = \n| established     = \n| vice_chancellor = Dr.Bahauddeen Muhammed Nadwi <ref name=M500 />\n| city            = [[Tirurangadi]]\n| state           = [[Kerala]]\n| country         = [[India]]\n| website         = {{url|www.dhiu.in}}\n}}\n'''Darul Huda Islamic University''' is a national [[Islamic university|Islamic University]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://twocircles.net/2017dec25/419290.html|title=Darul Huda Islamic University to start educational institutes in four states \u2013 TwoCircles.net|last=TwoCircles.net|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thepeninsulaqatar.com/article/07/12/2017/Seminar-on-renovation-of-Islamic-education-in-S-Asia|title=Renovation of Islamic Education in South Asia|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-04|website=ThePeninsulaQatar}}</ref> based at [[Chemmad]] in the district of [[Malappuram]], [[Kerala]], [[India]]. The university is a member of the [[League of Islamic Universities]] and the [[Federation of the universities of the islamic world]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thepeninsulaqatar.com/article/07/12/2017/Seminar-on-renovation-of-Islamic-education-in-S-Asia|title=Renovation of Islamic Education in South Asia|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-04|website=ThePeninsulaQatar}}</ref><ref>{{Cite press release|url=http://www.jaihoon.com/6722.htm|title=Darul Huda gains another International recognition|language=en-US|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref> Prof. Dr. Bahauddeen Muhammed Nadwi is the Vice-Chancellor<ref name=M500>{{Cite web|url=https://www.themuslim500.com/profiles/bahauddeen-muhammed-jamaluddeen-nadwi/|title=Bahauddeen Muhammed Jamaluddeen Nadwi|website=The Muslim 500|language=en-US|access-date=16 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.themuslim500.com/profiles/bahauddeen-muhammed-jamaluddeen-nadwi/|title=Teaching Atheism at government cost \u2013 Dr Bahauddin nadwi|date=30 March 2011|website=JAIHOON.TV|language=en-US|access-date=29 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://mhrd.gov.in/sites/upload_files/mhrd/files/upload_document/NMCMEResolution_2011.pdf | title=Reconstitution of the National Monitoring Committee for Minorities' Education (NMCME) on expiry of tenure | date=23 December 2011 | publisher=Government of India, Ministry of Human Resource Development, Department of Education, Minority Cell | accessdate=14 August 2019 }}</ref> and [[Sayed Hyderali Shihab Thangal]] serves as its Chancellor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dhiu.in/administration#top-officials/|title=Chancellor, University webportal|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> \n\nDarul Huda was established in 1986 as an Islamic college, with the name Darul Huda Islamic Academy.  Currently, it has affiliated institutes all across Kerala and other states in India including [[Maharashtra]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[West Bengal]], [[Karnataka]] and [[Assam]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thepeninsulaqatar.com/article/07/12/2017/Seminar-on-renovation-of-Islamic-education-in-S-Asia|title=Renovation of Islamic Education in South Asia|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-04|website=ThePeninsulaQatar}}</ref> Besides the Malayalam speaking students of Kerala, it also serves [[Urdu]] speaking students of north India.<ref name=\"HefnerZaman2010\">{{cite book|author1=Robert W. Hefner|author2=Muhammad Qasim Zaman|title=Schooling Islam: The Culture and Politics of Modern Muslim Education|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SzCfcQuQKx0C&pg=PA98|date=16 December 2010|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-1-4008-3745-8|pages=98\u2013}}</ref> According to the [[]], the university has produced hundreds of proficient Islamic scholars aims at empowering the community with scholars versed in Islamic knowledge and modern sciences.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thepeninsulaqatar.com/article/07/12/2017/Seminar-on-renovation-of-Islamic-education-in-S-Asia|title=Renovation of Islamic Education in South Asia|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-04|website=ThePeninsulaQatar}}</ref> The university's contribution in the empowerment of Muslim community is also well recognized.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kochipost.com/2019/10/15/how-utilitarianism-is-gnawing-at-minority-education-in-kerala/|title=How Utilitarianism is gnawing at Minority Education in Kerala|date=15 October 2019|website=KochiPost}}</ref>\n\n\n==Academic Courses== \n[[File: Bahahuddin Usthad at Convocation.jpg|alt=|thumb|right|250px| Dr. Bahauddeen Muhammed Nadwi delivers Vice Chancellor's address at the University's Convocation ceremony.]]\n[[File: DarulHudaIslamicUniversity.JPG|alt=|thumb|right|250px| Postgraduate Building of the University.]]\nDarul Huda University offers a 12-year course that integrates religious education with  general subjects<ref>{{cite book |title=History of muslim educational institutions in Kerala during 20th century |location=Cahpter 3 |page=145 |url=https://shodhganga.inflibnet.ac.in/bitstream/10603/8473/13/13_chapter%203.pdf#page=48 |accessdate=29 February 2020 |quote=Established in 1986, Darul Huda has set up a number of feeder institutions from where it takes the brightest students after completion of their primary schooling and takes them through 12 years of grueling Islamic and modern education.}}</ref>. The basic 12- year course is divided into four stages - a 2-year Preparatory course, a 4-year Secondary course, a 4-year Degree course and a 2-year PG course. The syllabus includes religious subjects such as Quran, Tajweed, Hadith, Usul ul-Hadith, Fiqh, Usul ul-Fiqh, Aqeeda, Tasawwuf, Nahvu, Sarf, Mantiq, Balagha and comparative studies of various religions, as well as secular subjects like Maths, Social Sciences, History, Physics, Chemistry and Biology. In addition to this, Arabic, Urdu, English, and [[Malayalam]] are taught.\n\nThe government-approved degrees in secular subjects are taught in English .<ref>{{Cite journal|author=Pedersen, Gry Hvass|year=2016|title=The Case of Jamia Millia Islamia in New Delhi|journal=Review of Middle East Studies|volume=50|issue=1|pages=28\u201337|jstor=26250536|doi=10.1017/rms.2016.73}}</ref>\n\n==Women's education==\nFathima Zahra Islamic Women's College is a girls institute specially for women. It was established in 1992.{{Citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n\n==Academic collaboration==\nDarul Huda has memberships in  federations of global Islamic Universities including  the Federation of the Universities of the Islamic World <ref>[http://www.isesco.org.ma/fuiw.org/upload/en/conference_general/2013_en.pdf List of Members of FUIW|]</ref>  The university has signed  [[Memorandum of Understanding]]s with  Indian universities like [[Aligarh Muslim University]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amu.ac.in/newdata/depttmom/5286.pdf|title=AMU}}</ref> [[Jamia Millia Islamia]]<ref>[https://upload.indiacode.nic.in/showfile?actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00022_198858_1517807325657&type=ordinance&filename=Ordinance%205%20Part%20I%20(Academic)%20JMI%20(Admission%20and%20enrollment%20of%20students).pdf ADMISSION AND ENROLLMENT OF STUDENTS, Jamia Millia]</ref>, [[Khwaja Moinuddin Chishti Urdu, Arabi-Farsi University]] <ref>[http://uafulucknow.ac.in/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/prospect_.pdf UAFULuucknow]</ref> and [[Jawaharlal Nehru University]] <ref>[https://jnu.ac.in/admission/JNU%20Prospectus%202019-20.pdf] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190817202048/http://jnu.ac.in/admission/JNU%20Prospectus%202019-20.pdf |date=17 August 2019 }},</ref> [[Delhi University]] among others<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.milligazette.com/news/1632-darul-huda-islamic-uni-in-kerala|title=Darul Huda Islamic Uni. in Kerala|first=The Milli|last=Gazette|date=17 June 2011|website=www.milligazette.com}}</ref> and with international universities including [[International Islamic University Malaysia]] and with the University of Kuwait. The [[Maulana Azad National Urdu University]] recognizes the courses of Darul Huda.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://twocircles.net/2015jun30/1435682381.html|title=Darul Huda Islamic University, Kerala signs MoU with Kuwait University \u2013 TwoCircles.net}}</ref><ref>https://manuucoe.in/RegularAdmission/assets/pdf/List%20of%20Madarsa%20Programs%20approved%20by%20the%20University%20for%20Admissions%202019.pdf</ref>\n\n== Student activities ==\nFacilities for extracurricular activities like debates, discussions, oratory training, computer studies, and sports are also provided through its students Union (DSU).{{Citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n\n===Thelitcham Monthly===\n{{main|Thelitcham Monthly}}\n[[Thelitcham Monthly]], is a student-focused magazine published by this University. Doctor Bahaudheen Nadwi is the editor-in-chief of the magazine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/blogs/tracking-indian-communities/homosexuality-is-a-psychological-disorder/|title=HOMOSEXUALITY is a psychological disorder |date=7 September 2019|website=Times of India Blog|language=en-US|access-date=29 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/kochi/2015/jul/08/Students-Magazine-Thelitchamon-Transgender-Rights-Kicks-off-Debate-780691.html|title=Students Magazine 'Thelitcham'on Transgender Rights Kicks off Debate|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=29 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Annahda Arabic bi-monthly===\nAnnahda is an Arabic bi-monthly magazine launched in August 2006 which is edited by Doctor N.A Muhammed Abdul Khader, Professor Emeritus at the University of Calicut.{{Citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n\n==Affiliated Colleges==\nBesides the Central Campus DHIU encompasses up to twenty affiliated colleges.<ref name=\"Riaz2014\">{{cite book|author=S. Riaz|title=New Islamic Schools: Tradition, Modernity, and Class in Urban Pakistan|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CKGxAwAAQBAJ&pg=PT27|date=20 May 2014|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan US|isbn=978-1-137-38247-4|pages=27\u2013}}</ref>\nIt has established an off-campus in October 2011 at Bhimpur in [[Birbhum]] district of West Bengal state. The campus is affiliated up to degree college level.\n\n==Publications==\n===Translations===\nTranslation of the Qur\u2019an in Malayalam is being published by DH Press.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n\n===Journals===\nIslamic Insight International Journal of Islamic Studies is a double-blind peer-reviewed journal with ISSN 2581-3269, published by the Faculty of Islamics and Human Sciences at the University. The subjects covered are Qur\u2019anic Studies, Hadith Studies, Islamic Jurisprudence, Islamic Theology, Islamic Mysticism, Philosophy, Comparative Religion, Islamic Social Sciences and Culture of Muslims.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n\n==Alumni== \nDr. Faisal KP Hudawi was appointed as Director of Aligarh Muslim University Kerala branch recently in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/education/dr-faisal-kp-appointed-director-of-amu-centre-malappuram-2030475|title=Doctor Faisal KP Appointed Director Of AMU Malappuram Centre|website=NDTV.com}}</ref> \n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Darul Huda Islamic Academy}}\n*[http://www.dhiu.in/ Official Webportal of Darul Huda]\n\n[[Category:Madrasas in India]]\n[[Category:1986 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Madrassas in Kerala]]\n[[Category:Islamic universities and colleges in India]]\n[[Category:Islam in Kerala]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Advert|date=December 2019}}\n{{Confusing|date=December 2019}}\n{{Peacock|date=December 2019}}\n{{Undisclosed paid|date=December 2019}}\n{{Original research|date=December 2019}}\n}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name            = Darul Huda Islamic University\n| logo_size       = \n| native_name     = \u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629 \u062f\u0627\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0647\u062f\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645\u064a\u0629\n| image_name      = Darul Huda.jpg\n| caption         = Darul Huda Islamic University, [[Tirurangadi]]\n| image_size      = \n| established     = \n| vice_chancellor = Dr.Bahauddeen Muhammed Nadwi <ref name=M500 />\n| city            = [[Tirurangadi]]\n| state           = [[Kerala]]\n| country         = [[India]]\n| website         = {{url|www.dhiu.in}}\n}}\n'''Darul Huda Islamic University''' is a Private [[Islamic university|Islamic University]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://twocircles.net/2017dec25/419290.html|title=Darul Huda Islamic University to start educational institutes in four states \u2013 TwoCircles.net|last=TwoCircles.net|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref> based at [[Tirurangadi]] in the district of [[Malappuram]], [[Kerala]], [[India]]. The university is a member of the [[League of Islamic Universities]].<ref>{{Cite press release|url=http://www.jaihoon.com/6722.htm|title=Darul Huda gains another International recognition|language=en-US|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref> Dr. Bahaudheen Muhammed Nadwi is the Vice-Chancellor<ref name=M500>{{Cite web|url=https://www.themuslim500.com/profiles/bahauddeen-muhammed-jamaluddeen-nadwi/|title=Bahauddeen Muhammed Jamaluddeen Nadwi|website=The Muslim 500|language=en-US|access-date=16 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.themuslim500.com/profiles/bahauddeen-muhammed-jamaluddeen-nadwi/|title=Teaching Atheism at government cost \u2013 Dr Bahauddin nadwi|date=30 March 2011|website=JAIHOON.TV|language=en-US|access-date=29 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://mhrd.gov.in/sites/upload_files/mhrd/files/upload_document/NMCMEResolution_2011.pdf | title=Reconstitution of the National Monitoring Committee for Minorities' Education (NMCME) on expiry of tenure | date=23 December 2011 | publisher=Government of India, Ministry of Human Resource Development, Department of Education, Minority Cell | accessdate=14 August 2019 }}</ref> and [[Cherussery Zainuddeen Musliyar]] was its Chancellor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kochipost.com/2019/10/15/how-utilitarianism-is-gnawing-at-minority-education-in-kerala/|title=How Utilitarianism is gnawing at Minority Education in Kerala|date=15 October 2019|website=KochiPost|language=en-US|access-date=29 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://english.mathrubhumi.com/amp/news/kerala/cherussery-sainudeen-musaliar-passes-away-english-news-1.873132|title=Cherussery Sainudeen Musaliar passes away{{!}} Cherussery Sainudheen Musaliar{{!}} Samastha Kerala JemEiathul Ulma {{!}} Mathrubhumi Online|website=english.mathrubhumi.com|access-date=28 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nDarul Huda was established in 1986 as an Islamic college, with the name Darul Huda Islamic Academy. It is being run by Samastha Kerala Jamaitul Ulema Samastha (EK faction).{{Citation needed|date=December 2019}} It was established as a University, not as Madarsa. It also serves [[Urdu]] speaking students of north India.<ref name=\"HefnerZaman2010\">{{cite book|author1=Robert W. Hefner|author2=Muhammad Qasim Zaman|title=Schooling Islam: The Culture and Politics of Modern Muslim Education|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SzCfcQuQKx0C&pg=PA98|date=16 December 2010|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-1-4008-3745-8|pages=98\u2013}}</ref> According to the ''Kochi Post'', it imparts education to  capable but underprivileged boys for secondary and higher education.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kochipost.com/2019/10/15/how-utilitarianism-is-gnawing-at-minority-education-in-kerala/|title=How Utilitarianism is gnawing at Minority Education in Kerala|date=15 October 2019|website=KochiPost}}</ref>\n\n==Academic Courses== \n[[File: Bahahuddin Usthad at Convocation.jpg|alt=|thumb|right|250px| Darul Huda Convocation ceremony.]]\n[[File: DHIU CHEMMAD.JPG|alt=|thumb|right|250px| Darul Huda Islamic University.]]\nDar ul-Huda offers a 12-year course that integrates religious education with  general subjects<ref>{{cite book |title=History of muslim educational institutions in Kerala during 20th century |location=Cahpter 3 |page=145 |url=https://shodhganga.inflibnet.ac.in/bitstream/10603/8473/13/13_chapter%203.pdf#page=48 |accessdate=29 February 2020 |quote=Established in 1986, Darul Huda has set up a number of feeder institutions from where it takes the brightest students after completion of their primary schooling and takes them through 12 years of grueling Islamic and modern education.}}</ref>. The basic 12- year course is divided into four stages - a 2-year Preparatory course, a 4-year Secondary course, a 4-year Degree course and a 2-year PG course. The syllabus includes religious subjects such as Quran, Tajweed, Hadith, Usul ul-Hadith, Fiqh, Usul ul-Fiqh, Aqeeda, Tasawwuf, Nahvu, Sarf, Mantiq, Balagha and comparative studies of various religions, as well as secular subjects like Maths, Social Sciences, History, Physics, Chemistry and Biology. In addition to this, Arabic, Urdu, English, and [[Malayalam]] are taught.\n\nThe government-approved degrees in secular subjects are taught in English .<ref>{{Cite journal|author=Pedersen, Gry Hvass|year=2016|title=The Case of Jamia Millia Islamia in New Delhi|journal=Review of Middle East Studies|volume=50|issue=1|pages=28\u201337|jstor=26250536|doi=10.1017/rms.2016.73}}</ref>\n\n==Women's education==\nFathima Zahra Islamic Women's College is an girls institute specially for women. It was established in 1992.{{Citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n\n==Academic colloboration==\nDarul Huda has memberships in  federations of global Islamic Universities including  the Federation of the Universities of the Islamic World <ref>[http://www.isesco.org.ma/fuiw.org/upload/en/conference_general/2013_en.pdf List of Members of FUIW|]</ref>  The university has signed  [[Memorandum of Understanding]]s with  Indian universities like [[Aligarh Muslim University]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amu.ac.in/newdata/depttmom/5286.pdf|title=AMU}}</ref> [[Jamia Millia Islamia]]<ref>[https://upload.indiacode.nic.in/showfile?actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00022_198858_1517807325657&type=ordinance&filename=Ordinance%205%20Part%20I%20(Academic)%20JMI%20(Admission%20and%20enrollment%20of%20students).pdf ADMISSION AND ENROLLMENT OF STUDENTS, Jamia Millia]</ref>, [[Khwaja Moinuddin Chishti Urdu, Arabi-Farsi University]] <ref>[http://uafulucknow.ac.in/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/prospect_.pdf UAFULuucknow]</ref> and [[Jawaharlal Nehru University]] <ref>[https://jnu.ac.in/admission/JNU%20Prospectus%202019-20.pdf] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190817202048/http://jnu.ac.in/admission/JNU%20Prospectus%202019-20.pdf |date=17 August 2019 }},</ref> [[Delhi University]] among others<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.milligazette.com/news/1632-darul-huda-islamic-uni-in-kerala|title=Darul Huda Islamic Uni. in Kerala|first=The Milli|last=Gazette|date=17 June 2011|website=www.milligazette.com}}</ref> and with international universities including [[International Islamic University Malaysia]] and with the University of Kuwait. The [[Maulana Azad National Urdu University]] recognizes the courses of Darul Huda.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://twocircles.net/2015jun30/1435682381.html|title=Darul Huda Islamic University, Kerala signs MoU with Kuwait University \u2013 TwoCircles.net}}</ref><ref>https://manuucoe.in/RegularAdmission/assets/pdf/List%20of%20Madarsa%20Programs%20approved%20by%20the%20University%20for%20Admissions%202019.pdf</ref>\n\n== Student activities ==\nFacilities for extracurricular activities like debates, discussions, oratory training, computer studies, and sports are also provided through its students Union (DSU).{{Citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n\n===Thelitcham Monthly===\n{{main|Thelitcham Monthly}}\n[[Thelitcham Monthly]], is a student-focused magazine published by this University. Doctor Bahaudheen Nadwi is the editor-in-chief of the magazine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/blogs/tracking-indian-communities/homosexuality-is-a-psychological-disorder/|title=HOMOSEXUALITY is a psychological disorder |date=7 September 2019|website=Times of India Blog|language=en-US|access-date=29 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/kochi/2015/jul/08/Students-Magazine-Thelitchamon-Transgender-Rights-Kicks-off-Debate-780691.html|title=Students Magazine 'Thelitcham'on Transgender Rights Kicks off Debate|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=29 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Annahda Arabic bi-monthly===\nAnnahda is an Arabic bi-monthly magazine launched in August 2006 which is edited by Doctor N.A Muhammed Abdul Khader, Professor Emeritus at the University of Calicut.{{Citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n\n==Affiliated Colleges==\nBesides the Central Campus DHIU encompasses up to twenty affiliated colleges.<ref name=\"Riaz2014\">{{cite book|author=S. Riaz|title=New Islamic Schools: Tradition, Modernity, and Class in Urban Pakistan|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CKGxAwAAQBAJ&pg=PT27|date=20 May 2014|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan US|isbn=978-1-137-38247-4|pages=27\u2013}}</ref>\nIt has established an off-campus in October 2011 at Bhimpur in [[Birbhum]] district of West Bengal state. The campus is affiliated up to degree college level.\n\n==Publications==\n===Translations===\nTranslation of the Qur\u2019an in Malayalam is being published by DH Press.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n\n===Journals===\nIslamic Insight International Journal of Islamic Studies is a double-blind peer-reviewed journal with ISSN 2581-3269, published by the Faculty of Islamics and Human Sciences at the University. The subjects covered are Qur\u2019anic Studies, Hadith Studies, Islamic Jurisprudence, Islamic Theology, Islamic Mysticism, Philosophy, Comparative Religion, Islamic Social Sciences and Culture of Muslims.{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n\n==Alumni== \nDoctor Faisal KP Hudawi was appointed as Director of Aligarh Muslim University Kerala branch recently in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/education/dr-faisal-kp-appointed-director-of-amu-centre-malappuram-2030475|title=Doctor Faisal KP Appointed Director Of AMU Malappuram Centre|website=NDTV.com}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Darul Huda Islamic Academy}}\n*[http://www.dhiu.in/ Official Webportal of Darul Huda]\n\n[[Category:Madrasas in India]]\n[[Category:1986 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Madrassas in Kerala]]\n[[Category:Islamic universities and colleges in India]]\n[[Category:Islam in Kerala]]\n", "name_user": "Suhail hidaya", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Darul_Huda_Islamic_University"}
